      "text": "I pulled up late with the lights low\nStill got your name in my iPhone\nYou say I’m poison, I know\nBut you still sip when your eyes close\nWe go back and forth like waves do\nI run from love but I chase you\nI said I changed, that ain’t true\nI just hate the way I crave you\nYou hit my line when the bass drop\nI know your friends say I’m bad news\nBut when the night get too loud\nI’m still the one that you dance to\nI’m faded, you’re dangerous\nStill somehow my favorite\nWe break it, then save it\nThen wake up and say this",
      "lines": 16,
